description:
Responsibilities :

         Responsible for office administration works & documentation management of site office

Requirements :

         Form 5 graduate with HKCEE full cert, preferably have completed a post secondary; certificate programme on human resources management;
         Minimum 5 years' administrative experience;
         Site office experience is much preferred;
         Good command of both spoken & written English, Chinese
         Proficient in MS Office;
         Working on site office 
         Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Site Administrative Officer ; with less experience will be considered as Assistant Site Administrative Officer
         Immediate available is highly preferred
An attractive remuneration package will be offered to the successful candidate. To apply for the above position, please send your application with full resume, current and expected salary and contact number to Human Resources Department - E-mail via clicking "Apply Now"

工作內容及職責:

一般秘書職務;
協調及安排董事日常行程;
管理議程並安排會議及約會,會議記錄;
協助日常人力資源工作:籌辦培訓、招募、公司活動;
團隊業績報告追踪成員業績/獎項;
處理辦公室行政工作，包括訂購購文具、辦公室用品、同事出勤及假期紀錄等;
處理上級委派的其他工作

職位要求:

一年經驗或以上
專上教育或學士學位(商業/行政管理/人力資源/社會科學)
良好粵語、良好普通話、良好英文
懂讀寫中文及英文
懂Microsoft Office及中英文基本電腦操作

工作地點: 觀塘區

福利包括：

銀行假期、五天工作、醫療保障、提供員工早午膳、10天有薪年假、考試假、婚假、勤工獎。

 有意應徵者請把詳細的履歷發送給我們，請註明現職薪金和期望薪金。

The applicant must possess
a recognised degree;
a minimum of 3 years’ post-qualification work experience in institutional administration, preferably in vocational training bodies, educational institutions, public bodies or sizable organisations;
knowledge in construction and managerial accounting would be an advantage;
strong leadership, self-initiative and problem solving skills;
a high level of integrity and a strong sense of responsibility;
good communication and interpersonal skills;
a pro-active, resourceful and energetic character, and the ability to work independently with minimal supervision;
good knowledge and skills in Word, Excel, Powerpoint, English and Chinese word processing; and
a good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.
(Applicants who do not possess the required qualifications and / or experience may be considered for other positions within the organisation.)
Duties include
to oversee the daily operation of the Kowloon Bay Campus and lead the administration team to ensure smooth and effective operation;
to initiate, plan, manage and implement new development initiatives and improvement initiatives;
to assist the adoption of computerisation and carry out user acceptance test in system implementation;
to assist in promoting construction training including the marketing of construction related courses to the general public and the stakeholders of the construction industry;
to assist in obtaining qualifications recognition from local and overseas professional organisations, educational institutions and government authorities;
to perform secretariat duties for related task forces, promotion events, seminars, conferences, and any other relevant activities;
to prepare for the annual budget;
to help maintain the Kowloon Bay Campus in a clean and tidy state of operation and help task the security guards and cleaners;
to act as duty-in-charge during non-office hour operation; and
to carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by the Executive Director.
Applications
The position is on a renewable fixed-term contract (subject to performance and operational needs) for a period of 2 years.
Please click the below “Apply Online” to complete the application form and upload the updated curriculum vitae, the results of English and Chinese Language obtained in public examinations, current and expected salary together with a covering letter stating one’s suitability for the job on or before 27 January 2022.

Responsibilities

Responsible for full spectrum of general office administration supports in a professional manner, including maintenance, procurement of office suppliers and other administrative or support functions required;
Maintain staff record and HR filing system;
Take up ad-hoc assignments as required.

Requirement

Diploma or above;
1 - 2 years relevant experience;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Good command of written and spoken in both English and Cantonese;
Proficient in MS Office applications, English and Chinese Word Processing;
Immediate availability is an absolute advantage;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Administration Officer.

Please send your application with resume and expected salary to The HR Manager, Dah Chong Hong Ltd, 8/F, DCH Building, 20 Kai Cheung Road, Kowloon Bay or submit your application online by clicking "Apply Now" or send your resume to the email address stated in our company description.

Information provided will be for the purpose of selection within the company and only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be retained for a maximum period of 6 months.

Job Responsibilities:

Oversee the administrative matters, course management and coordination of the Programmes, to maintain an effective day-to-day operation of the programmes, such as student records, examinations, graduation matters, course materials and lectures preparation;
Reports to the Head of School regarding programme operation matters such as managing academic related tasks and student affairs;
Priorities key tasks, allocating duties to academic & programme staff within the Institution and in accordance with Institution policies and procedures;
Assist in reviewing and developing/ monitoring the implementation of policies and procedures;
Play a key part in implementation of the QA processes & Accreditation exercise;
Undertake committee work in various meetings, committees and boards;
Develop and comply various programme related reports and statistics for management review;
Perform any other duties as assigned by the Supervisor.

Job Requirements:

Minimum Bachelor Degree (preferably with post graduate degree) &/or Professional qualifications in related subject areas;
Minimum 4 years working experience in higher education programmes &/or programme administration & management in which at least 2 years in a supervisory role;
Excellent command in both written & spoken English and Chinese;
Demonstrated ability to scope work, generate work plans and manage to deadlines;
A good team leader with strong communication, interpersonal and analytical skills;
Self-motivated, organized, detail-oriented and capable in multi-tasking;
Presentable, personable and patient personality;
Proficientin computer software applications, such as Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint;
Experience in managing programme management team and working with students will be a definite advantage;
Immediate availability is highly preferred.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, and the collected data will also be considered for other suitable positions available in our Company.

Only short-listed candidates will be notified.

(Ref: AO/EA (REG) 2022-01-14)

Responsibilities:
provide administrative and logistic support on programme development (programme accreditation and reaccreditation), synchronisation and standardisation of programme accreditation documents, meetings and other accreditation matters;
assist in the preparation of programme accreditation documents;
handle and maintain central filing on programme development and programme quality assurance matters; and
serve as secretary to committees and working groups.

Applicants should:
possess a recognised degree, preferably with 2 years of relevant working experience;
be a fast learner, proactive, self-motivated, a good team player and able to work independently with strong sense of responsibility;
possess good interpersonal and communication skills;
have a good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua); and
have good PC knowledge including MS Word, Excel and Chinese Processing.
Work experience in the tertiary education sector will be an advantage.  Applicants with less experience will be considered as Executive Assistant.


Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested applicant should visit this link https://recruit.hsu.edu.hk/ and apply on or before 30 January 2022.  The University reserves the right not to fill the position in this exercise.
Applicants who are not invited to an interview within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful.  All information received will be treated in strict confidence, and the data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  The Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request.
