KNOWLEDGE TRANSFER AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP OFFICE

Assistant Manager (two posts) (Ref. 22011407-JCS)

Duties

The appointees will work under the Intellectual Property Management and Commercialisation section and be required to:

(a) assist in the execution of Intellectual Property (IP) management, commercialisation, due diligence and invention disclosures;

(b) prepare written evidence-based recommendations on the potential commercialisation opportunity or impact based upon due diligence;

(c) conduct patent search, prepare patent applications and provide support to office actions;

(d) work closely with internal and external stakeholders such as inventors, patent attorney, funders and external consultants on issues related to IP management and commercialisation;

(e) provide support to IP system, database management and other IP related matters; and

(f) perform any other duties as may be assigned by the Director of the Office or his delegates.

Qualifications

Applicants should:

(a) have a recognised degree in a relevant area of Science and/or Engineering plus at least five years’ relevant post-qualification working experience preferably in business, intellectual property and/or law;

(b) have a good understanding of technology transfer, business development and licensing;

(c) be highly motivated, result-oriented and able to work independently;

(d) have a good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua); and

(e) possess excellent interpersonal and communication skills.

Applicants who have responded to the previous advertisement need not re-apply.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered. Appointment will be on a one-year gratuity-bearing contract. Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now". Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms. If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process. Consideration of applications will commence on 21 January 2022 until the positions are filled. The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Responsible for the procurement of office supplies, furniture & equipment and administrative services;
Monitor suppliers’ performance and quality on regular basis and perform benchmarking analysis to optimize company’s internal purchasing policy;
Manage general administration services including reception and company vehicles;
Manage application and renewal of vehicle license and insurance;
Handle ad hoc tasks and projects as assigned.

Requirements

University degree or equivalent;
Minimum 5 years’ relevant experience including at least 2 years’ experience in supervisory role in reputable organization;
Experience in managing e-procurement system is in advantage; 
Good command in written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications & technically sound in office workflow system
Self-motivated, reliable, service mindset and possess can-do attitude;
Good management and supervisory skills.
We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department



by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

